Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Thus the fiber consists of 4 irreducible components passing \
through the p1 - point .\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " We use the notation of Proposition A.3. We may  eliminate the orbifold \
coordinates s246, S125, u1 near the p1-point. Then s123 is one of the \
orbifold coordinates. Therefore ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["E", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ab86cf41-cfe0-c641-a18e-3b1a35a1212c"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["|", "F"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9876f019-acea-924a-9c03-b7245c4f87d5"],
 "=",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["\[DoubleStruckCapitalP]",
     FontWeight->"Bold"], "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a3578792-bdba-524e-bc91-e3f60d343b4e"],
 ". The roots of the above degree 4 polynomial represents the intersections \
between  ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["E", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fe511ca0-6bee-2d4c-87c0-6512806928cc"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["|", "F"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9fd1ab0f-7dc6-324a-af0d-73834c1ef7af"],
 " and the strict transforms of the irreducible components  of the fiber \
passing through the p1 - point. Thus the condition of (6) of Proposition A.3 \
holds. We may easily check that the other conditions of  Proposition A.3 \
hold.\n Similar properties hold for other singularities on the exceptional \
divisor (we will omit the explanation below). "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9836936080653667`*^9, 3.983693637910389*^9}, {
   3.9836936731947193`*^9, 3.9836936758209896`*^9}, 3.9836951588525143`*^9, {
   3.9843711883744545`*^9, 3.98437118971776*^9}, 3.9843712285611153`*^9, {
   3.984382294546339*^9, 3.9843823004738483`*^9}, {3.9843826740442085`*^9, 
   3.9843827328917446`*^9}, {3.984382866085413*^9, 3.9843831280500374`*^9}, {
   3.984628185458027*^9, 3.9846282507791996`*^9}, {3.9851178070608635`*^9, 
   3.985117867497061*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"81deedbe-49b4-944e-8394-\
46da9ba1431a"],

